Sublimetext2-Subversion-plugin
Plugin to provide subversion support to Sublimetext2

Written by Timmy SjÃ¶stedt and Patrik Ring

INSTALL
	1. Add the file subversion.py to (...)/Packages/User

	2. Put the following lines in your local .sublime-keymap (Preferences->User key bindings)
		{ "keys": ["ctrl+alt+c"], "command": "subversion", "args": {"cmd": "commit"} },
		{ "keys": ["ctrl+alt+u"], "command": "subversion", "args": {"cmd": "update"} },	
		{ "keys": ["ctrl+alt+a"], "command": "subversion", "args": {"cmd": "add"} },
		{ "keys": ["ctrl+alt+f"], "command": "subversion", "args": {"cmd": "togglefolders"} }
	
	3. ???
	4. PROFIT!!!
